<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1066,2012]" box="[197,928,1146,1172]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,1146,1172]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Description.</emphasis>
Male: body length 
<quantity box="[579,672,1146,1172]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity box="[831,924,1146,1172]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1066,2012]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Frons and face shiny brown. Frons slightly wider than width of anterior ocellus, sides subparallel, with two setae. Face slightly longer and about half width of frons. Proboscis light-yellow, length equal to height of head. Palpus brown, with one small and almost apical seta. Ocellar tubercule with vitreous light-yellow ocellus; two ocellar setae parallel; two proclinate postocellar setae. Antenna entirely brown with lighter scape; scape and pedicel medially verticillate; flagellum about four times longer than scape and pedicel combined. Postcranium shiny brown, with distinct brown setae and gray pruinescence; one pair of parallel vertical setae; postocellar setae distinct, arranged in complete single series with dorsal setae stronger. Gena and postgena with brown setae and sparse gray pruinescence. Thorax shiny brown, with conspicuous postsutural gray pruinescence. Thoracic setae: 
<number box="[469,484,1506,1532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="4.0">4</number>
slender ktg; 
<number box="[640,655,1506,1532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="4.0">4</number>
sctl, larger internal pair; aprn and prepm broken; 
<number box="[1251,1266,1506,1532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
pprn; 
<number box="[1345,1359,1506,1532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0">2</number>
acr; 
<number box="[1421,1436,1506,1532]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="4.0">4</number>
dc; 
<number box="[193,208,1546,1572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
spal presut; spal psut broken; 
<number box="[561,576,1546,1572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0">2</number>
ntpl; 
<number box="[643,658,1546,1572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
pal. Legs with coxae, trochanters and basal fifth of femora yellow, remaining segments brown. 
<collectingCountry box="[481,540,1586,1612]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia and hind basal tarsomere with long dorsal setae. All legs with short distinct setae. Wing hyaline with inconspicuous pterostigma; anal lobe wide (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1112,1626,1652]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="34.[151,255,1559,1583]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1535]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1436,194,1535]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 18. Wings of Porphyrochora (Diptera, Empididae), holotype male; a, Porphyrochroa aliena sp. nov.; b, P. amazonica sp. nov.; c, P. bifida sp. nov.; d, P. cercosingularis sp. nov.; e, P. dactiloides sp. nov.; f, P. d i s t i n c t a sp. nov.; g, P. epandrialis sp. nov.; h, P. grandis sp. nov.; i, P. longiseta sp. nov.; j, P. manauara sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/183632/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1081,1112,1626,1652]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.8" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="g" value="18.0">18</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g). Halter brown. Abdomen shiny brown, with metallic blue luster in diverse light incidence angles. Sternites shiny brown. Tergite 
<number box="[1361,1376,1666,1692]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
with pair of posteroventral protuberances (Fig. 
<number box="[643,659,1706,1732]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
a); tergite 
<number box="[776,790,1706,1732]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
truncated anteriorly and smaller than former ones (Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,1746,1772]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
a); sternite 
<number box="[299,314,1746,1772]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
sub-square and inclined in lateral view (Figs. 
<number box="[863,879,1746,1772]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
b; c); sternite 
<number box="[1042,1057,1746,1772]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
wide, with long setae (Fig. 
<number box="[1389,1405,1746,1772]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
b). Terminalia: hypandrium without setae (Figs. 
<number box="[690,706,1786,1812]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
d; h). Cercus elongate in lateral view, with ventral projection (Figs. 
<number box="[226,242,1826,1852]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
d; g). Epandrium projected anteriorly and superiorly, with setae on dorsal region (Fig. 
<number box="[1252,1268,1826,1852]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
e); ejaculatory apodeme with three projections in anterior view (Fig. 
<number box="[800,815,1866,1892]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
f); subepandrial sclerite with base shorter than arms (Fig. 
<date box="[214,240,1906,1932]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<number box="[214,230,1906,1932]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
i
</date>
).
</paragraph>
